Sentencas: Cathode materials are pivotal in advancing ceramic fuel cell (CFC) technology.
Titulo: Evaluation of the electrocatalytic performance of a novel nanocomposite cathode material for ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: However, they still suffer from insufficient oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) activity and a high thermal expansion coefficient (TEC).
Titulo: Evaluation of the electrocatalytic performance of a novel nanocomposite cathode material for ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: In this study, we develop a thermodynamically stable self-ordered nanocomposite cathode material with the unique composition, BaCo0.5Ce0.3Fe0.1Yb0.1O3-delta (BCCFYb).
Titulo: Evaluation of the electrocatalytic performance of a novel nanocomposite cathode material for ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: Upon calcination, the precursor material separates into a host cubic and ancillary rhombohedral phase.
Titulo: Evaluation of the electrocatalytic performance of a novel nanocomposite cathode material for ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: We compare the performance of the triple ionic and electronic (O2-/ H+/e- ) conducting BCCFYb to that of cobalt-rich oxide-ion and electron (O2-/e- ) conducting BaCo0.833Yb0.167O3-delta (BCYb), cerium-rich proton and electronic (H+/e-) conducting BaCe0.75Fe0.25O3-delta (BCF), and Co-Ce-rich triple ionic and electronic (O2- /H+/e- ) conducting BaCo0.833Yb0.167O3-delta - BaCe0.75Fe0.25O3-delta (BCYb-BCF) traditional composite materials.
Titulo: Evaluation of the electrocatalytic performance of a novel nanocomposite cathode material for ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: The BCCFYb demonstrates a low TEC, good operational stability, and superior cathodic performance in both oxygen ion- and proton-conducting CFC modes, making it a promising cathode material for ceramic fuel cells.
Titulo: Evaluation of the electrocatalytic performance of a novel nanocomposite cathode material for ceramic fuel cells
